snippet.textDisplay:
Idk who is gonna read this or care but I'll share it.

In my life I've felt connected to people I haven't met in ways I can't describe, and Mac is one of them. But the thing is, even though I enjoyed his music and knew of him, he wasn't largely on my radar, certainly didn't come to my mind often.
The night Mac died, I had this incredibly vivid dream, that I was in this 4th dimensional space, and I was focused on this electronic space-suit type mask. The mask was panneled with mini screens per se, and the eyes lit up with white light and the mask "turned on" and I could see Mac Miller's face, like the mask was his face suddenly. And it was so poignant. And then I woke up to the news that he had died. To see this video and the space man, something more definitely was waiting for him on the other side. I love you, mac.
